reviews.review_text:
nothing but highest rating just a little light on the setlist: 
01SHAKEDOWN - 02WALKIN - 03FAR FROM ME - 04CANDYMAN - 05MOBILE BLUES - 06RAMBLE ON ROSE - 07SATURDAY NITE - 08STEP BACK - 09EOTW - 10ESTIMATED - 11CRAZY FINGERS - 12UJB - 13DRUMS1 - 14DRUMS2 - 15SPACE - 16TAKE U HOME - 17I NEED A MIRACLE INCL.GDTRFB - 18THROWING STONES - 19THE LAST TIME - 20GOODNIGHT


this is one of the finest shows i experienced so far! checking the list of alternatives of this date imo this item gets the cup. it's so crisp and fine tuned, i suggest this to get published one day! or maybe somewhere there's a well trained crack able to matrix it? would be worth the work! phil's bass meanders round and jerry's playing and voice seldomly came out so near-to-the-ear ;-D 

we bid you goodnight is one of the funniest performances i remember :-)))

but then - i admit to be a brent fan! - listen to the key frenzies, just a little bit more than one week before mydland went. in parts this show seems to be something like 'brent mydland band covering some of the greatest hits of the GD'! sorry - but he simply plays his a** off, and when i realized this i couldn't but DL this simply in-grate-able good show.

IT'S SO FINE - DON'T YOU DARE MISS IT!

07-14-90 track listing correction:
17: miracle->gdtrfb
18: throwing stones
19: love light
20: last time
21: bid you goodnight

great show for brent fans, just 12 days before his death, and played very well. worth a listen for sure!!
